  <h2>Favorite Senior Portrait Locations in Brighton</h2>

  <h3>Huron Meadows Metropark</h3>
  <p>Wide open meadows, mature tree canopy, and that gorgeous boardwalk over the wetlands. Huron Meadows is one of my all-time favorite shooting locations. The variety within one park is incredible — we can get a wildflower field, a wooded path, and a lakeside shot all within a 10-minute walk.</p>

  <h3>Brighton Mill Pond</h3>
  <p>Right in the heart of downtown Brighton, the Mill Pond gives us water reflections, a covered bridge, and manicured green space. It's walkable from the shops and restaurants on Main Street, which means we can mix in some urban texture if you want variety.</p>

  <h3>Island Lake Recreation Area</h3>
  <p>This is the spot for seniors who want that open, airy, natural feel. Rolling hills, tall grasses, and wide-open sky. At golden hour, the light across these fields is magazine-worthy. The Kensington-to-Island Lake trail connector gives us miles of options.</p>

  <h3>Downtown Brighton</h3>
  <p>Main Street Brighton has murals, brick facades, and great light in the late afternoon. If you want a mix of natural and urban looks, we can start downtown and drive 5 minutes to one of the parks for a completely different vibe.</p>

  <h2>What Your Senior Session Looks Like</h2>
  <p>Every session starts with a consultation — I want to know what you're into, what your style is, what you want to remember about this year. Then we plan outfits, timing, and locations. On session day, I guide you through everything. No stiff posing, no awkward silence. Just real moments and great light.</p>

  <p>Most sessions include 2-3 outfit changes and last about 90 minutes. You'll receive a private online gallery within 2-3 weeks with full print release.</p>

